      "comment": "PINK POPPY CLUB (1) had been racing well with a TG1-4W win three back then placed next time before missing the frame latest at Murray Bridge Straight. Better than last run and makes appeal this time. PURE GOUT (8) returned a better run last time, finishing in the money (22.70) at Broken Hill behind Archer Twelve in a Grade 5. Expecting another good run. MASTER KILCOY (2) was narrowly beaten when placing two back but missed the frame latest finishing fourth (20.12) in a TG1-4W at this track. Well placed here and can atone this time. ELEGANT FLINT (4) justified the favourite's tag last time and is a major player again.",
